`crates/ctx-context/` is the ctx CLI/hook crate as a whole: a read-only tool that resolves a repo path to its chain of rollup/intent/leaf context documents and serves that chain as rendered text, either printed directly or injected via a Claude Code `PostToolUse` hook. Depending on this crate as a binary gets you the `ctx` CLI and the hook entry point; both are fail-open and never panic.

`src/` holds the full pipeline (`repo_path` → `chain` → `serve` → `session`) behind a single `Env` I/O abstraction and a single `CtxError` error type, plus the CLI/hook wiring that calls it. `tests/` is the integration suite that pins the external contract of that pipeline — chain ordering and path-escape rejection, the STALE/NEVER-GENERATED/absent-marker freshness trichotomy, and cross-process session dedup — using independently-reimplemented `FakeEnv`s that must stay behaviorally aligned with each other and with the real `Env`.

The tightest cross-cutting fact spanning both subtrees: chain node ordering, `NodeKind::label()` values, and the rendered `=== id [kind] ===` format are contracts shared by `src`'s renderer and `tests`' fixtures — changing one without the other breaks the suite silently in spirit even where assertions still pass. Similarly, "absent" is always a structured marker/enum on both sides, never an `Err`, and source files never appear as chain node ids. The crate-wide invariant is strict read/serve/inject: nothing here writes `.ctx` or `rollup.ctx` content.